e xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104thr1665702690548.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/thr1665702690548.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/thr1665702690548.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"thr1665702690548\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"thr1665702690548__retrieve_reconnect_236707\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Reconnect data loaded from a disconnected record set (XML, JSON, or Struct) with the occurrences in a database or component.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"thr1665702690548__topic_d76550e1_d76551e1_d76552e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"thr1665702690548__p_d76553e1_d76554e1_d76555e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">retrieve/reconnect</span> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntityName</var>}</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"thr1665702690548__section_w2080ab1b7b5_w2081ab1b7_w2082ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"thr1665702690548__p_d76556e1_d76557e1_d76558e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">retrieve/reconnect CUSTOMER.SALES</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"thr1665702690548__topic_d50297e1_d50298e1_d50299e1_d50300e1_d50301e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1224393e77\">\n                       \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7271e1_d7272e1_d7273e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7271e1_d7272e1_d7273e1__entry__1\">\n Parameter\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7271e1_d7272e1_d7273e1__entry__2\">\n Data Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7271e1_d7272e1_d7273e1__entry__3\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7271e1_d7272e1_d7273e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntityName</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7271e1_d7272e1_d7273e1__entry__2\">\n String\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7271e1_d7272e1_d7273e1__entry__3\">\n Entity included in the component structure of a component.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"thr1665702690548__topic_d50302e1_d50303e1_d50304e1_d50305e1_d50306e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1224393e131\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7274e1_d7275e1_d7276e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7274e1_d7275e1_d7276e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7274e1_d7275e1_d7276e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7274e1_d7275e1_d7276e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7274e1_d7275e1_d7276e1__entry__2\">\n Occurrence was successfully reconnected.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7274e1_d7275e1_d7276e1__entry__1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&gt;0</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"thr1665702690548__table_d7274e1_d7275e1_d7276e1__entry__2\">\n Number of errors encountered.\n <p class=\"p\">In this context, an error is defined as the number of times an error trigger returned a negative value.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"thr1665702690548__topic_d50307e1_d50308e1_d50309e1_d50310e1_d50311e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1224393e195\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"thr1665702690548__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"thr1665702690548__topic_d50312e1_d50313e1_d50314e1_d50315e1_d50316e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1224393e204\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"thr1665702690548__p_d76574e1_d76575e1_d76576e1\">Used after the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">xmlload</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">webload</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">structToComponent</span> statements, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">retrieve/reconnect</span> command resolves the modification state information stored in the occurrence metadata. The procedure followed for each occurrence depends on the value of the occurrence modification state. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dvf1665702566367.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dvf1665702566367.html\" title=\"To manage the exchange of data between components and a database, metadata is maintained about occurrences, such as whether the occurrence is new or already stored in a database. This occurs transparently, so that a programmer generally does not have to handle data state.\">Occurrence Metadata for Reconnect</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kpa1665702574811.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kpa1665702574811.html\" title=\"The reconnect process merges data in disconnected occurrences (in XML, JSON, or Structs) with data in the component, and resolves the state information that is stored in the modification status attributes. It removes duplicates of occurrences, removes occurrences marked for deletion from the component, and sets the appropriate modification flags.\">Reconnect Process</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"thr1665702690548__p_d76577e1_d76578e1_d76579e1\">The behavior of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">retrieve/reconnect</span> is the same as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">reconnect</span>. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qnx1665702574893.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qnx1665702574893.html\" title=\"Reconnect data loaded from a disconnected record set (XML, JSON, or Struct) with the occurrences in a component and database (if connected).\">reconnect</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"thr1665702690548__section_lwx_z5l_zbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1224393e256\">Example: Receiving an XML Stream</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following code shows an operation that receives an XML stream, and\n            loads the data from the XML into the component’s data structure.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"thr1665702690548__pre_i33_1vl_zbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">operation XMLIN\n; This operation receives and\n; reconnects an XML stream.\nparams\n xmlstream [DTD:ABCDTD.ABC] MYSTREAM : IN\nendparams\nclear\nxmlload MYSTREAM, \"DTD:ABCDTD.ABC\"\nretrieve/reconnect\n...\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zom1665702566196.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Disconnected Record Sets</a><p>Disconnected record sets provide a way for components to maintain and share data and its state (such as whether the data has been modified) even when a connection to a database is not available. They are typically used for communication between web components (server pages and web services) and are usually implemented as XML, JSON, or Uniface Structs.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lln1665702574971.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>structToComponent</a><p>Converts data from a Struct or collection of Structs into the entities and occurrences in the component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fyg1714374176100.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>webload</a><p>Loads data from a JSON stream in $webinfo(\"data\") into a component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vuu1665702574732.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>xmlload</a><p>Load data from an XML stream into occurrences drawn on the component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fpz1719812992669.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$occvalidation</a><p>Check whether an occurrence requires validation.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/atw1665702600492.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$instancemod</a><p>Return or set the modification status of data in the current component instance.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uni1718715029734.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$formmod (deprecated)</a><p>Return the modification status of data in the current Form component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qdc1665702602510.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$fieldvalidation</a><p>Identify whether a field requires validation.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/roo1720021541651.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>fieldsyntax (deprecated)</a><p>Set the syntax attributes of the specified field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/blp1718891086730.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$fieldsyntax</a><p>ProcScript function to change the Field Syntax property of a field.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532355\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532355\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "retrieve/reconnect Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Reconnect data loaded from a disconnected record set (XML, JSON, or Struct) with the occurrences in a database or component. retrieve/reconnect { EntityName } Example: retrieve/reconnect CUSTOMER.SALES Parameters Table 1. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description EntityName String Entity included in the component structure of a component. Return Values Table 2. Values returned in $status Value Meaning 0 Occurrence was successfully reconnected. >0 Number of errors encountered. In this context, an error is defined as the number of times an error trigger returned a negative value. Use Allowed in all component types. Description Used after the xmlload , webload , structToComponent statements, the retrieve/reconnect command resolves the modification state information stored in the occurrence metadata. The procedure followed for each occurrence depends on the value of the occurrence modification state. For more information, see Occurrence Metadata for Reconnect and Reconnect Process . The behavior of retrieve/reconnect is the same as reconnect . For more information, see reconnect . Example: Receiving an XML Stream The following code shows an operation that receives an XML stream, and loads the data from the XML into the component’s data structure. operation XMLIN ; This operation receives and ; reconnects an XML stream. params xmlstream [DTD:ABCDTD.ABC] MYSTREAM : IN endparams clear xmlload MYSTREAM, \"DTD:ABCDTD.ABC\" retrieve/reconnect ... Copy Related Links Disconnected Record Sets Disconnected record sets provide a way for components to maintain and share data and its state (such as whether the data has been modified) even when a connection to a database is not available. They are typically used for communication between web components (server pages and web services) and are usually implemented as XML, JSON, or Uniface Structs. structToComponent Converts data from a Struct or collection of Structs into the entities and occurrences in the component. webload Loads data from a JSON stream in $webinfo(\"data\") into a component. xmlload Load data from an XML stream into occurrences drawn on the component. $occvalidation Check whether an occurrence requires validation. $instancemod Return or set the modification status of data in the current component instance. $formmod (deprecated) Return the modification status of data in the current Form component. $fieldvalidation Identify whether a field requires validation. fieldsyntax (deprecated) Set the syntax attributes of the specified field. $fieldsyntax ProcScript function to change the Field Syntax property of a field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}